She said, "Let's see who can hold the most of the blanket. The winner gets to sleep comfortably, and the loser has to tell a joke." Dudu agreed, thinking he could easily win. They both pulled the blanket from each other, trying to cover themselves. But Bubu was smarter and faster than Dudu. She quickly wrapped herself in the blanket, leaving Dudu with only a small corner. Dudu realized he had lost and sighed. He said, "OK, you win. Here is my joke: What do you call a fish that wears glasses? A see-fish!" Bubu laughed and hugged Dudu. She said, "That was a silly joke, but I love you anyway. Come here, I'll share the blanket with you." They cuddled together under the blanket and fell asleep happily.
